The paper discusses the use of Capsule Neural Networks, which are a type of Convolutional Neural Network (cs.CV) that simulate the visual processing system of the human brain. The paper also introduces psychological theories related to cognitive consistency, which are relevant to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The optimization of the routing algorithm of Capsnet is a machine learning task (cs.LG) and the paper involves experiments with text data, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper uses artificial neural networks (ANNs) to estimate or generate unknown approximation functions, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.NE).
